---
// src/pages/medicare-savings-programs-utah.astro — Dual-Eligible silo spoke (M6).
// Medicare Savings Programs (QMB, SLMB, QI) consolidated. Limits from
// annualMedicareData (single-sourced, correct).
import ArticlePage from '../components/layout/ArticlePage.astro';
import { figuresFor } from '../data/annualMedicareData';
import { usd } from '../lib/formatters';
import type { PageContext } from '../types/Page';

const f = figuresFor();
const year = f.year;
const msp = f.medicareSavingsPrograms;

const rows = [
  { program: 'QMB', name: 'Qualified Medicare Beneficiary', pays: 'Part A & B premiums, plus deductibles, coinsurance, and copays', limits: msp.qmb },
  { program: 'SLMB', name: 'Specified Low-Income Medicare Beneficiary', pays: 'Part B premium', limits: msp.slmb },
  { program: 'QI', name: 'Qualifying Individual', pays: 'Part B premium (limited funds — apply early each year)', limits: msp.qi },
];

const context: PageContext = {
  page: {
    title: `Medicare Savings Programs in Utah ${year} — QMB, SLMB, QI | Vernal Medicare`,
    heading: 'Medicare Savings Programs (QMB, SLMB, QI)',
    description: `Medicare Savings Programs can pay your Part B premium — and QMB pays much more. See ${year} Utah income and resource limits for QMB, SLMB, and QI, and how to apply.`,
    taxonomy: { silo: 'dual-eligible', tags: ['msp', 'qmb', 'slmb', 'qi', 'medicaid', 'costs', 'part-b'] },
    summary: `Medicare Savings Programs (MSPs) are state-run programs that help pay your Medicare costs. QMB pays your Part A & B premiums plus deductibles and coinsurance; SLMB and QI pay your Part B premium (${usd(f.partB.premium, { cents: true })}/mo in ${year}). Qualifying also unlocks Extra Help for drugs automatically.`,
    faqs: [
      {
        question: 'What is the difference between QMB, SLMB, and QI?',
        answer: `All three help pay Medicare costs, with rising income limits. QMB pays the most — your Part A and Part B premiums plus deductibles, coinsurance, and copays. SLMB and QI pay your Part B premium (${usd(f.partB.premium, { cents: true })}/month in ${year}). QI has limited funding, so apply early in the year.`,
      },
      {
        question: `What are the ${year} income limits in Utah?`,
        answer: `Monthly income limits for ${year} are roughly ${usd(msp.qmb.individual)} (QMB), ${usd(msp.slmb.individual)} (SLMB), and ${usd(msp.qi.individual)} (QI) for a single person, and higher for couples. Countable resources must be under about ${usd(msp.resources.individual)} (single) or ${usd(msp.resources.couple)} (married). Limits are higher than many expect.`,
      },
      {
        question: 'Does an MSP also help with drug costs?',
        answer: 'Yes. If you qualify for any Medicare Savings Program, you automatically qualify for Extra Help (the Part D Low-Income Subsidy), which lowers or eliminates your prescription drug premium, deductible, and copays.',
      },
    ],
    sources: [
      { title: 'Medicare Savings Programs', url: 'https://www.medicare.gov/basics/costs/help/medicare-savings-programs', publisher: 'Medicare.gov' },
      { title: 'Utah Medicaid / Department of Workforce Services', url: 'https://medicaid.utah.gov/', publisher: 'State of Utah' },
    ],
    nextSteps: [
      {
        when: 'If your monthly income is near these limits,',
        action: `apply anyway — the limits are higher than most people expect, and qualifying also unlocks Extra Help. We can check all of it for free.`,
      },
    ],
  },
  meta: {
    canonical: 'https://vernalmedicare.com/medicare-savings-programs-utah.html',
    ogType: 'article',
    ogTitle: 'Medicare Savings Programs (QMB, SLMB, QI) — Utah',
    ogDescription: `${year} Utah income & resource limits for QMB, SLMB, and QI, and how they help pay your Medicare costs.`,
  },
  author: 'rocco',
  datePublished: '2026-06-30',
  lastUpdated: '2026-06-30',
  breadcrumb: [
    { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { name: 'Dual Eligible & Medicaid', href: '/dual-eligible.html' },
    { name: 'Medicare Savings Programs', href: '/medicare-savings-programs-utah.html' },
  ],
};
---

<ArticlePage context={context}>
  <p>If Medicare's monthly premiums and out-of-pocket costs strain your budget, a <strong>Medicare Savings Program (MSP)</strong> may cover them for you. These are state-run programs — in Utah, through Medicaid / the Department of Workforce Services — and qualifying also unlocks <a href="medicare-extra-help-utah.html">Extra Help</a> for prescriptions automatically.</p>

  <h2>The Three Programs</h2>
  <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:1.5rem 0;">
    <thead>
      <tr style="background:#0b2c45; color:#fff;">
        <th style="padding:12px; text-align:left; border:1px solid #ddd;">Program</th>
        <th style="padding:12px; text-align:left; border:1px solid #ddd;">What it pays</th>
        <th style="padding:12px; text-align:left; border:1px solid #ddd;">Monthly income (single)</th>
        <th style="padding:12px; text-align:left; border:1px solid #ddd;">Monthly income (married)</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {rows.map((r) => (
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ddd;"><strong>{r.program}</strong><br /><span style="font-size:.85rem; color:#555;">{r.name}</span></td>
          <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ddd;">{r.pays}</td>
          <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ddd;">{usd(r.limits.individual)}</td>
          <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ddd;">{usd(r.limits.couple)}</td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p style="color:#555; font-size:.95rem;">Resource (asset) limits for {year}: about {usd(msp.resources.individual)} for a single person and {usd(msp.resources.couple)} for a married couple. Your home and one car generally don't count.</p>

  <h2>Why It's Worth Applying</h2>
  <p>QMB is especially valuable — it can eliminate your Part B premium ({usd(f.partB.premium, { cents: true })}/month in {year}) <em>and</em> cover deductibles and coinsurance, effectively acting like a supplement at no cost to you. Even SLMB or QI, which "only" pay the Part B premium, put real money back in your pocket every month.</p>

  <p>Because income limits are higher than most people assume — and because qualifying automatically triggers <a href="medicare-extra-help-utah.html">Extra Help</a> for drugs — it's almost always worth checking. Start with the <a href="dual-eligible.html">dual-eligible overview</a>, or call us and we'll check every program you might qualify for at once.</p>
</ArticlePage>
